com.datastax.dse.driver.api.core.metadata.schema

Interface DseFunctionMetadata

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Describable, FunctionMetadata

    public interface DseFunctionMetadata
extends FunctionMetadata
    Specialized function metadata for DSE.

    It adds support for the DSE-specific DETERMINISTIC and MONOTONIC keywords.

      • getDeterministic

        default Optional<Boolean> getDeterministic()
        Indicates if this function is deterministic. A deterministic function means that given a particular input, the function will always produce the same output.

        This method returns empty if this information was not found in the system tables, regardless of the actual function characteristics; this is the case for all versions of DSE older than 6.0.0.

        Returns:
        Whether or not this function is deterministic; or empty if such information is not available in the system tables.

      • isMonotonic

        @Deprecated
boolean isMonotonic()
        Deprecated. use getMonotonicity() instead.

      • getMonotonicity

        default Optional<DseFunctionMetadata.Monotonicity> getMonotonicity()
        Returns this function's DseFunctionMetadata.Monotonicity.

        A function can be either:

        • fully monotonic. In that case, this method returns DseFunctionMetadata.Monotonicity.FULLY_MONOTONIC, and getMonotonicArgumentNames() returns all the arguments;
        • partially monotonic, meaning that partial application over some of the arguments is monotonic. Currently (DSE 6.0.0), CQL only allows partial monotonicity on exactly one argument. This may change in a future CQL version. In that case, this method returns DseFunctionMetadata.Monotonicity.PARTIALLY_MONOTONIC, and getMonotonicArgumentNames() returns a singleton list;
        • not monotonic. In that case, this method return DseFunctionMetadata.Monotonicity.NOT_MONOTONIC and getMonotonicArgumentNames() returns an empty list.

        Full monotonicity is required to use the function in a GROUP BY clause.

        This method returns empty if this information was not found in the system tables, regardless of the actual function characteristics; this is the case for all versions of DSE older than 6.0.0.

        Returns:
        this function's DseFunctionMetadata.Monotonicity; or empty if such information is not available in the system tables.

      • getMonotonicArgumentNames

        @NonNull
List<CqlIdentifier> getMonotonicArgumentNames()
        Returns a list of argument names that are monotonic.

        See getMonotonicity() for explanations on monotonicity, and the possible values returned by this method.

        NOTE: For versions of DSE older than 6.0.0, this method will always return an empty list, regardless of the actual function characteristics.

        Returns:
        the argument names that the function is monotonic on.
